OL,3,CNigel Farage offered Sunderland
OL,4,CStadium of Light visit by club director
OL,6,FSartori first met Farage in Davos
OL,7,Fearlier this year while both men
OL,8,Fattended the World Economic Forum.
OL,10,FHe expressed his admiration for the
OL,11,FReform UK leader and suggested he
OL,12,Fvisit Sunderland's stadium, according
OL,13,Fto one figure present at the meeting.
OL,15,FSartori, who was born in Uruguay but
OL,16,Fgrew up in Europe, made his money as
OL,17,Fthe founder of Union Capital Group,
OL,18,Fone of Uruguay's biggest investment
OL,19,Fcompanies.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/11
